Caption: Fig. 1. The Duet interface consists of a settings menu (a) an attribute list (b), a small table (c), group and attribute shelves (d), a result panel (e), and a relationship map (f). The user is comparing New England colleges and Southeast colleges (d) and the similar and different attributes are shown in the result panel (e). She is revisiting the stored recommended attributes by clicking on a link between two nodes (g). The stored attributes are displayed in the stored recommendation panel (h).
